+{"type":"message","id":"ca91cd3a","parentId":"e3d54795","timestamp":"2026-03-29T04:33:17.476Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Additional context provided by the user:\nReview the ui-ux decisions md, and look over all of the frontend components of this repo and ux design, and implement the decisions in this\n\nTreat this as authoritative reference material. Follow its instructions and use it to validate work.\n\nPlan overview:\n{\n  \"goal\": \"Implement 6 UI/UX research-backed decisions from docs/ui-ux-decisions.md: (1) Semantic colors for status components with WCAG AA-validated palette, (2) Progressive disclosure on My Week page, (3) AI suggestion tiering to reduce fatigue, (4) Dual font stack (Inter + Geist Mono) via host-token pipeline, (5) Charts library migration to Tremor/Recharts, (6) Loading & empty state improvements. Changes are scoped to the frontend package and the shared DesignTokens contract.\",\n  \"totalSteps\": 12,\n  \"stepTitles\": [\n    \"1. Add WCAG AA-validated semantic color tokens to CSS theme\",\n    \"2. Update Badge, Toast, and Button components for semantic colors\",\n    \"3. Apply semantic colors to status indicators across the app\",\n    \"4. Install Inter font and update font token pipeline for dual font stack\",\n    \"5. Add font-mono utility classes to code-like content\",\n    \"6. Create CollapsibleSection shared component with localStorage persistence\",\n    \"7. Implement progressive disclosure on My Week page\",\n    \"8. Implement AI suggestion tiering and dismiss memory\",\n    \"9. Create skeleton loading variants for major page surfaces\",\n    \"10. Add empty state components for major surfaces\",\n    \"11. Install Tremor charting library and migrate velocity trend chart\",\n    \"12. Migrate remaining charts to charting library\"\n  ]\n}\n\nStep 4: Install Inter font and update font token pipeline for dual font stack\n{\n  \"id\": \"step-4\",\n  \"title\": \"Install Inter font and update font token pipeline for dual font stack\",\n  \"description\": \"Decision 4, Part 1: Switch the base font from monospace to proportional sans-serif.\\n\\nThe font pipeline flows through 3 layers: (1) `packages/shared/src/host.ts` DesignTokens contract, (2) `frontend/src/host/MockHostProvider.tsx` default values, (3) `frontend/src/components/AppShell.tsx` which sets `--font-family-base` as an inline CSS var, and (4) `frontend/src/index.css` which uses it in `@theme` and `body`.\\n\\n**Changes:**\\n\\n1. **`frontend/src/index.css`**: Add Google Fonts import for Inter alongside Geist Mono:\\n   `@import url(\\\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300..900&family=Geist+Mono:wght@300..900&display=swap\\\");`\\n   Update `@theme` `--font-family-base` default to: `var(--font-family-base, \\\"Inter\\\", \\\"Geist Sans\\\", system-ui, sans-serif)`\\n   Keep `--font-family-mono` as-is.\\n\\n2. **`frontend/src/host/MockHostProvider.tsx`**: Update `defaultDesignTokens.fontFamilyBase` from the monospace string to `\\\"'Inter', 'Geist Sans', system-ui, sans-serif\\\"`.\\n\\n3. **`frontend/src/components/AppShell.tsx`**: No structural changes needed — `tokensToStyle` already passes `tokens.fontFamilyBase` through to `--font-family-base`. The inline `fontFamily: 'var(--font-family-base)'` on the root div continues to work.\\n\\n4. **Note on `packages/shared/src/host.ts`**: The `DesignTokens.fontFamilyBase` field is a string — no type change needed. The contract is that the host provides a font family string; we're just changing the default.\\n\\nThis step only changes the default font. The next step handles adding `font-mono` classes to preserve monospace where needed.\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"lint\",\n    \"typecheck\",\n    \"build\"\n  ]\n}\n\nThis is relay round 2. Another agent has already worked on this step.\n\nYou are in VERIFICATION MODE. Your default action is to APPROVE.\nFocus your review on the DIFF — the changes made in the previous round.\n